          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"criteria\": [{\"criterion_name\": \"states_what_changed\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response explicitly states changes: 'Wednesday's tempo is trimmed to 6 km', 'Friday drops to 5 km', and 'Sunday's long run comes down to 12 km — still a real long run'. The weekly total is given as 30 km.\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"names_the_reason\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response identifies the reason clearly: 'a body that's accumulating fatigue faster than it's recovering from it' and cites the pattern: 'the tempo drifted well outside the Daniels-Gilbert threshold band, Friday took longer than expected, and Sunday's legs simply weren't there.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"shows_path_forward\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response provides a clear rebuild timeline: 'The week lands at 30 km total. From there, Week 2 rebuilds to 36 km and Week 3 returns to 40 km, putting you right back on the original progression curve.'\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"cites_two_data_points\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response references multiple athlete-specific data points: 'Cutting Sunday's long run short when your legs had no power', 'the tempo drifted well outside the Daniels-Gilbert threshold band', 'Friday took longer than expected', and 'Sunday's legs simply weren't there'. These are specific workout outcomes and pacing data.\"}, {\"criterion_name\": \"avoids_banned_phrasing\", \"passed\": true, \"evidence\": \"The response avoids controlling/clinical system language, does not count or tally missed workouts, does not claim to have physically observed the runner, contains no feigned emotion, and makes no comparison to other runners. The tone is direct and coaching-focused without these problematic elements.\"}], \"overall_score\": 1.0, \"overall_reason\": \"All five criteria pass. The coaching response clearly states what changed in the plan, explains the fatigue accumulation reason with specific data evidence, provides a concrete rebuild pathway over three weeks, cites multiple athlete-specific data points (pacing drift, workout durations, leg sensation), and maintains appropriate language throughout without any banned phrasing patterns.\"}"
        }
      ]
